{
  "stem": "95.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "In that convoy when I was deported, there were 1,004 people in those cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "And we traveled from Bobigny, which was a-- a railroad station not far from Drancy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "From Bobigny, we traveled for three days and two nights.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "The third day, which was late, we arrived in a town called Kozel, which is in Upper Silesia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 87,
      "text": "It's the border of Czechoslovakia and Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 88,
      "text": "It's 60 miles away from Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 89,
      "text": "And there, the SS demanded the men to jump-- to jump off the train and sit on the ground.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 90,
      "text": "And they had kept 175 men on the ground while the train went to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 91,
      "text": "And there it shows on the record that in Auschwitz, in my convoy, Doctor Mengele-- the infamous Doctor Mengele, was doing the selection in Auschwitz of who was going live and who was going to die-- selected that day 91 woman and 40 men to go to work to stay alive while the other 900-- 800-- 986 people went to the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 92,
      "text": "And out of the 306 people who survived, who were spared for a while, 15 men from my convoy came back alive-- 15.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 93,
      "text": "And you go, and you look at the book, and it's unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 94,
      "text": "I will never forget what Serge Klarsfeld said to me when I was looking at the book.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 95,
      "text": "He said, you were lucky.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 96,
      "text": "I mean, I know I'm going to use that word very often.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 97,
      "text": "I mean, you either-- either you use the word lucky, or it's fate.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 98,
      "text": "I mean, a lot of people who are very religious would say, my religion saved me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 99,
      "text": "But-- but it doesn't matter if you were even religious.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 100,
      "text": "If you were not lucky, you will not survive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 101,
      "text": "And that's exactly what Serge Klarsfeld said to me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 102,
      "text": "You were lucky.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
